    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Japanese plucked lutelike chordophones having two pairs of strings, a flat body of wood, a short fretted neck with lateral pegs, and a metal lamella affixed to the interior of the body.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cordófonos de pulsación japoneses tipo laúd con dos pares de cuerdas, un cuerpo plano de madera, un mástil corto con trastes y clavijas laterales, y una lámina de metal fijada en el interior del cuerpo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Japanse tokkelinstrumenten met twee paar snaren, een platte houten klankkast, een korte hals met fretten en schroeven opzij, en een metalen lamel die binnenin de klankkast is vastgemaakt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指類似魯特琴的日本弦鳴樂器，以撥弦方式彈奏，具有兩對琴弦、平坦的木製琴身、帶有側邊弦鈕及琴品的短琴頸，琴身內部另有金屬薄片。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gezupftes Lauteninstrument aus Japan mit zwei Saitenpaaren, einem flachen Resonanzkörper aus Holz, einem kurzen Hals mit Bünden und seitlichen Stimmwirbeln sowie einer Metalllamelle, die am Inneren des Klangkörpers befestigt ist.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
